Packages 
Package Description
com.whirvis.jraknet
JRakNet is a networking library for Java which implements the UDP based protocol RakNet.
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat  
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat.client  
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat.client.frame  
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat.protocol  
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat.server  
com.whirvis.jraknet.chat.server.command  
com.whirvis.jraknet.client
Components used to create RakNet clients.
com.whirvis.jraknet.client.peer
Components used by the RakNetClient in order to more easily establish connections with servers using the PeerFactory class.
com.whirvis.jraknet.discovery
Components used to discover RakNet servers on both local and external networks.
com.whirvis.jraknet.identifier
Classes used to create identifiers that describe servers or parse identifiers to get their information.
com.whirvis.jraknet.interactive  
com.whirvis.jraknet.map
Components used to create HashMap objects with the keys being native types such as byte, short, int, and long.
com.whirvis.jraknet.map.concurrent
Components used to create ConcurrentHashMap objects with the keys being native types such as byte, short, int, and long.
com.whirvis.jraknet.peer
Componenents used to interface with RakNet peers, connections to either a server or a client machine.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol
The packets and extra components required for communication between both the server and the client to be possible.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol.connection
The packets that are sent between the server and client during initial connection.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol.login
The packets that are sent between the server and client during login after initial connection has succeeded.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol.message
The internal packets necessary in order for basic messaging to occur after login.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol.message.acknowledge
The packets used to notify a peer of a packet either being received or lost in transmission.
com.whirvis.jraknet.protocol.status
The packets that are sent between the server and the client to determine one's status and descriptors.
com.whirvis.jraknet.server
Components used to create RakNet servers.
com.whirvis.jraknet.stream
Components used to allow a Packet to be used as an InputStream or OutputStream using its' getInputStream() and getOutputStream() methods.
com.whirvis.jraknet.windows
Components used to interface with Universal Windows Programs.
